comments.body:
Thanks for the heads up [~arpiagariu]. The code change looks good.  I'm not sure whether the unit test change is needed as the 2nd parameter of the FairCallQueue constructor is already based on per queue capacity. I would suggest we test with mock (e.g., mockito) to validate internal subqueue capacity allocation given different {{ipc.server.handler.queue.size}}.

{code}
-    fcq = new FairCallQueue<Schedulable>(2, 5, "ns", conf);
+    fcq = new FairCallQueue<Schedulable>(2, 10, "ns", conf);
{code}
